for the guilty ambition of the
rest
.
I apprehend madam,
said
Columbia, that you
mean the offspring of the Lord Guilford Dudley and
lady Jane. Cora informed me of their unfortunate
exaltation and confequent death; and I have no doubt
but the royal Elizabeth will,
should
she
ever have the
power,
restore
to him his rank and the fortunes of
