nobleman
of elevated rank and
splendid
fortune, as the
person
with whom he
wished
to
share
those
advantages
.
He
solicited
her hand, was encouraged by both
Mr. and Mrs. Oliver, but
resolutely
rejected by
Jessy
herself
.
My father, continued he, who (as I mentioned
before) has no will but his wife's, has
sent
the poor
girl into the country, debarring her of all
society
, and
declaring
she
shall
stay
there till
she
accepts his
Lordship
;
and I, who know her
disposition
, think that
sentence
is tantamount to
saying
she
shall
stay
there as
long as
she
lives.
She is right to
persevere
