said
Rachel, if
she
does not feel her heart
sufficiently
attached
to him to incline her to
share
his pains and
pleasures
through life. For of all the
miseries
that can
be endured by a human being,
sure
none can be
so
severe
as being obliged to
submit
to the whims and
