saw
her
must
fall in love with her, or that
they could not
pass
an hour in her company without
entertaining her with
praises
of her wit and beauty, and
complaints of their own
hopeless
passion
.
When the coach therefore
stopped
, and Rachel
asked
him to walk in, he eagerly availed
himself
of the
invitation; and after
sitting
with her till
she
was
summoned
