surrounded
her in the boxes was totally
unnoticed. But between the play and entertainment,
she
looked round on the glittering throng; and in the
stage
-box,
conversing
with attentive
carnestness
with
Y
an elegant and very young lady,
she
saw
Hamden
Auberry.
The lady laid her hand on his
shoulder
. Rachel
discovered
that her
seat
was uncomfortable.
Hamden
,
as he
conversed
,
twisted
a curl of her luxuriant
