round his fingers.
I declare I am out of patience, cried Rachel.
At what, ma'am? cried the officious Mr.
Spriggins
.
At the players,
said
she
; they are
so
tedious.
Yes, ma'am, replied Spriggins, they are to be
sure
a long while.
At that moment Hamden had taken the hand of
his fair companion and
pressed
it to his lips.
I cannot endure it any longer, cried Rachel,
the pit is
so
crowded, and it is
so
hot. Rachel
was not
easily
